-- FACTBOX-Apple's stock split among largest in S&P 500 since 1980
-- By Caroline Valetkevitch
-- Wed Apr 23, 2014 06:22PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, April 23 (Reuters) - Apple's seven-for-one stock split, announced after the market close Wednesday, is one of the largest stock splits in the history of the S&P 500 since 1980. Below is a list of the 11 largest splits for components in the benchmark index since 1980.

Namedate   splitratio  MasterCard  1/22/2014  10-1   Capital6/20/1994  10-1  Cities/ABCMetromedia  7/12/1983  10-1Apple  6/9/2014  7-1  CME Group   7/23/2012  5-1   Monsanto6/6/1996  5-1 CBS  10/19/1994 5-1   Teledyne3/2/1990  5-1   Unilever   6/29/1987  5-1   Marriott   5/20/1986  5-1   Superior   5/26/1981  5-1